Event_Description: The location ?Nuuk? is located in southwest Greenland and is a part of the Godthåbsfjord system. The fjord is almost ice free year round and is locally characterized by high biomass intertidal and subtidal biomass. This systems was chosen as a data from Greenland long-term climate-monitoring program focusing on ecosystem structures and dynamics is available from this site.
IUCN_Habitat_type: 9 - Marine Neritic (Submergent Nearshore Continental Shelf or Oceanic Island)
